<% content_for :title, "MRDBID Mushroom Identification Process Demo" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "See a public demonstration of the MRDBID mushroom identification word list process, downloadable tables, and editor forms." %>

<% github_repo_url = "https://github.com/mrdbidwill/mrdbid" %>

<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 space-y-8">
  <section class="border border-green-300 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-green-800 mb-2">Public demo</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">A Universal Mushroom Identification Word List</h1>
    <div class="max-w-4xl space-y-4 text-gray-800 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        MRDBID is intended to promote a common process for recording mushroom identification data.
        The central idea is simple: use a searchable word list of mushroom characters, store values in structured tables,
        and keep the character list editable as better mycological knowledge is contributed.
      </p>
      <p>
        This page separates the two workflows: the end user entering data for their own mushrooms, and the editor/admin
        maintaining the database tables that make the forms accurate and useful.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <%= link_to "Browse Character Catalog", mr_characters_path,
          class: "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-green-700 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-green-800" %>
      <%= link_to "Download Free Files", "#downloads",
          class: "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-blue-700 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-blue-800" %>
      <%= link_to "View GitHub Repository", github_repo_url,
          target: "_blank",
          rel: "noopener",
          class: "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-gray-800 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-gray-900" %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
    <div class="border border-blue-200 rounded-lg bg-blue-50 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Simple Search-Style Input</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        A Google-style character search lets users type what they observed, then select a standardized field such as cap width,
        gill attachment, stem surface, or spore print color.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-lg bg-green-50 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Existing Downloadable Tables</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        The character lists, supporting source tables, and guide spreadsheets already exist and can be downloaded for review,
        reuse, correction, or extension.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-amber-200 rounded-lg bg-amber-50 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Forms to Keep It Current</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        User-friendly forms already exist for entering mushroom data and for editors/admins to add, correct, and reorganize the
        underlying tables.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg bg-white overflow-hidden">
      <div class="bg-blue-100 px-5 py-4 border-b border-blue-200">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-800 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">End user example</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Input Data for My Mushroom</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 space-y-5">
        <div>
          <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Search mushroom characters</label>
          <div class="flex rounded-md border border-gray-300 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
            <div class="flex-1 px-4 py-3 text-gray-500">cap width</div>
            <div class="bg-blue-700 text-white px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold">Search</div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
            The user starts with familiar words. The application connects those words to standardized character rows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-gray-900">Selected character</div>
          <div class="p-4 space-y-3">
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Character</div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900">cap_width_mm</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Value entered</div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900">42 mm</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Stored result</div>
              <div class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-900 bg-gray-100 rounded px-3 py-2">mushroom_id + mr_character_id + value</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What the end user gets</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
            <li>A simple input process for their own observations.</li>
            <li>Consistent character names instead of ad hoc notes.</li>
            <li>Structured data that can later be searched, compared, copied, or exported.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg bg-white overflow-hidden">
      <div class="bg-amber-100 px-5 py-4 border-b border-amber-200">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-800 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Editor/admin example</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Maintain the Tables Behind the Form</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 space-y-5">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-gray-900">Character table form</div>
          <div class="p-4 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-500">Name</div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900">cap_surface_texture</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-500">Part</div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900">Cap</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-500">Observation method</div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900">Macro</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-500">Input type</div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900">Radio list</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-gray-900">Lookup value form</div>
          <div class="p-4">
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="rounded bg-blue-50 px-2 py-1 text-sm text-blue-800">glabrous</span>
              <span class="rounded bg-blue-50 px-2 py-1 text-sm text-blue-800">fibrillose</span>
              <span class="rounded bg-blue-50 px-2 py-1 text-sm text-blue-800">squamose</span>
              <span class="rounded bg-blue-50 px-2 py-1 text-sm text-blue-800">tomentose</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
              Editors/admins can add, edit, and source the values that appear in end-user forms.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What editors/admins maintain</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
            <li>Character names and definitions.</li>
            <li>Parts, observation methods, input types, and source data.</li>
            <li>Allowed values and lookup lists used by the end-user forms.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg bg-white overflow-hidden">
    <div class="bg-gray-100 px-5 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Read-Only Demo Output</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">Example of how entered data becomes a consistent mushroom character record.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200">
        <thead class="bg-gray-50">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-600 uppercase">Part</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-600 uppercase">Character</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-600 uppercase">User Value</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-600 uppercase">Table/Form Source</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Cap</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">cap_width_mm</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">42 mm</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">Numeric character definition</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Cap</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">cap_surface_texture</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">fibrillose</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">Lookup values maintained by editor/admin forms</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Gills</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">gill_attachment</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">adnate</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">Standard value list</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Spores</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">spore_print_color</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">white</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">Reusable character and lookup table rows</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg bg-white p-5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Live Reference Data</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-5">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-3">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900"><%= number_with_delimiter(@character_count) %></div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">characters</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-3">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900"><%= number_with_delimiter(@lookup_item_count) %></div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">lookup values</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-3">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900"><%= number_with_delimiter(@inaturalist_field_count) %></div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">iNaturalist fields</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <% if @sample_characters.any? %>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <% @sample_characters.each do |character| %>
            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded p-3">
              <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900"><%= character.name %></div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                <%= character.part&.name || "Part not set" %> /
                <%= character.observation_method&.name || "Method not set" %> /
                <%= character.display_option&.name || "Input type not set" %>
              </div>
              <% if character.lookup_items.any? %>
                <div class="mt-2 flex flex-wrap gap-1">
                  <% character.lookup_items.first(6).each do |item| %>
                    <span class="rounded bg-blue-50 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-blue-800"><%= item.name %></span>
                  <% end %>
                </div>
              <% end %>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      <% else %>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          The public catalog is available even when these exact demo character names are not present.
        </p>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg bg-white p-5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Video Overview</h2>
      <div class="aspect-video w-full rounded bg-gray-900 flex items-center justify-center text-center px-6">
        <div>
          <div class="text-white text-lg font-semibold">YouTube video placeholder</div>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mt-2">
            Embed the short overview here when the video is ready.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <p>
          A short video can show both sides of the process: end users entering mushroom data, and editors/admins maintaining
          the tables that make the form reliable.
        </p>
        <p>
          Suggested length: two to four minutes. Show the search-style input, the pre-existing tables, and the forms used to
          keep the word list correct.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="downloads" class="border border-green-300 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Free Downloads Available Now</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-800 mb-5">
      The database guides, source files, and application code are available now for free download. The CSV files can be opened
      in Excel and used as spreadsheet guides for reviewing and improving the <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">mr_characters</code>
      table and related source data.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <%= link_to "/docs/mr_characters_source_ORIGINAL.csv",
          class: "block border border-green-200 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 hover:bg-green-50" do %>
        <div class="font-semibold text-green-800">Download mr_characters guide</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Original Excel-compatible CSV guide for the character list.</div>
      <% end %>

      <%= link_to "/docs/mr_characters_source_parts.csv",
          class: "block border border-green-200 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 hover:bg-green-50" do %>
        <div class="font-semibold text-green-800">Download character parts guide</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Spreadsheet guide connecting characters to mushroom parts.</div>
      <% end %>

      <%= link_to "/docs/parts.csv",
          class: "block border border-green-200 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 hover:bg-green-50" do %>
        <div class="font-semibold text-green-800">Download parts table</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Excel-compatible CSV for the parts table.</div>
      <% end %>

      <%= link_to "/docs/types.csv",
          class: "block border border-green-200 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 hover:bg-green-50" do %>
        <div class="font-semibold text-green-800">Download types table</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Excel-compatible CSV for type/source reference data.</div>
      <% end %>

      <%= link_to inaturalist_observation_fields_path,
          class: "block border border-blue-200 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 hover:bg-blue-50" do %>
        <div class="font-semibold text-blue-800">Browse and download iNaturalist fields</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Public searchable field database with CSV and JSON download options.</div>
      <% end %>

      <%= link_to github_repo_url,
          target: "_blank",
          rel: "noopener",
          class: "block border border-gray-300 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 hover:bg-gray-50" do %>
        <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900">View all code and data on GitHub</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">The application repository is public for review and download.</div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How Visitors Can Help</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-gray-800">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Review the word list</h3>
        <p class="text-sm">Find missing characters, unclear names, duplicate ideas, or better option sets.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Test the workflow idea</h3>
        <p class="text-sm">Decide whether this process could fit Mushroom Observer, iNaturalist, MycoMap, or another site.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Suggest improvements</h3>
        <p class="text-sm">Use the contact page to send corrections, sources, and practical workflow feedback.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-5">
      <%= link_to "Contact MRDBID", contact_path,
          class: "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-blue-700 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-blue-800" %>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
